Why prediction is powerful
When people hear that ChatGPT or another large language model (LLM) is =E2=
=80=9Cjust predicting the next word,=E2=80=9D it sounds almost trivial=E2=
=80=94how could that produce essays, code, jokes, or business plans?=20
The trick is scale and structure. By training on gigantic amounts of text, =
an LLM learns the statistical fingerprints of language: grammar, facts, rea=
soning patterns, even cultural style. At run-time it doesn=E2=80=99t look u=
p an answer in a database; instead it builds the answer token-by-token, eac=
h choice conditioned on everything typed so far. Because the model has inge=
sted trillions of examples, these conditional probabilities encode an enorm=
